The Senate on Wednesday resumed but suspended its plenary till Thursday January 17,  in honour of a member of the House of Representatives, Abayomi Adeola, who died on December 30, 2018. Wednesday’s plenary lasted about 25 minutes after a motion by Francis Alimikhena that the adjournment be made in honour of the late lawmaker. Abayomi represented Ibeju Lekki Federal Constituency of Lagos State.  He died at a private health facility in Lagos after a brief illness on December 30, 2018. He had won his party’s ticket for a third term before his death. Meanwhile, the Senate observed a minute silence in his honour on Wednesday before adjourning, after a voice vote. The lawmakers met last at the Red Chamber on December 20, 2018  when the bade themselves farewell for the Christmas and new year festivities. 